u.seg: A man climbed in a tree
who was picking up things (= pears),
he put his things in a basket.

spanGrp.span: a man who had a goat

u.seg: a man who had a goat
A boy who had a bicycle came and

spanGrp.span: A boy who had a bicycle came and
while he was glancing at the man several times,

u.seg: while he was glancing at the man several times,
it seemed to me he hesitated to take things from the basket.

spanGrp.span: naːt doːr jhakistib isoːgagidna dheː itʔi /
it seemed to me that he hesitated to take something.

u.seg: took the basket and went away with it.

spanGrp.span: took the basket and went away with it.

u.seg: passed him and stroke his hat down from him,

spanGrp.span: but I don’t know how she made it fall.

u.seg: But I don’t know how she made it fall.

spanGrp.span: hit a stone and fell down.

u.seg: hit a stone and fell down.
three boys went towards him, and

spanGrp.span: three boys went towards him, and
by dint of picking up well his things, they helped him, and

u.seg: by dint of picking up well his things, they helped him, and
Then, now, when he took his things from the basket, and left walking,

spanGrp.span: when he took his things from it, and left walking,
they played a flute at him, and
since his hat had fallen from him,

u.seg: since his hat had fallen from him,

spanGrp.span: when they give him the hat,

u.seg: when they give him the hat,

spanGrp.span: to each of them these things that he had,

u.seg: he gave each of them one of these things he had.

spanGrp.span: the goat that he had, the form

u.seg: the goat that he had, had the form of a dark goat, with small ears, (as if) it were kneeling (= smaller than normal).

spanGrp.span: I thought it was a mountain goat.

u.seg: I thought it was a mountain goat.
